{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_017DvFSLoJ3Fpanf72EA9ULR","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Machine Config Operator (MCO) - Agent Entry Point\n2\t\n3\t## What This Component Does\n4\t\n5\tMCO manages node-level OS and configuration for OpenShift clusters. It owns the full lifecycle: generating Ignition configs from CRDs, rendering merged configs per pool, serving configs to bootstrapping nodes, and applying them on each node via a daemonset agent (MCD). It also supports on-cluster layering (OCL) where custom OS images are built from Containerfiles.\n6\t\n7\t## Repository Layout\n8\t\n9\t```\n10\tcmd/                          # 7 binaries (operator, controller, daemon, server, machine-os-builder, osimagestream, apiserver-watcher)\n11\tpkg/controller/               # All controllers (render, template, node, build, kubelet-config, container-runtime-config, bootimage, certrotation, pinnedimageset, drain, internalreleaseimage)\n12\tpkg/controller/common/        # Shared controller context, helpers, metrics, feature gates\n13\tpkg/daemon/                   # Machine Config Daemon - node agent that applies configs\n14\tpkg/server/                   # Machine Config Server - serves Ignition to bootstrapping nodes\n15\tpkg/operator/                 # Top-level operator sync, status, rendering\n16\tpkg/osimagestream/            # OS image stream provider and metadata\n17\ttemplates/                    # Ignition/systemd templates (common/, master/, worker/)\n18\tmanifests/                    # Deployed manifests, RBAC, ValidatingAdmissionPolicies\n19\ttest/                         # E2E suites (e2e-1of2, e2e-2of2, e2e-techpreview, e2e-bootstrap, e2e-ocl-*, e2e-single-node)\n20\ttest/framework/               # envtest setup, client initialization\n21\ttest/helpers/                 # Test builders, assertions, utilities\n22\tdevex/cmd/                    # Developer tools (mcdiff, mco-push, wait-for-mcp, etc.)\n23\thack/                         # Build, test, lint, template generation scripts\n24\tlib/                          # resourceapply, resourceread utilities\n25\t```\n26\t\n27\t## CRDs (API group: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1)\n28\t\n29\t| CRD | Purpose | Key Controller |\n30\t|-----|---------|----------------|\n31\t| MachineConfig | Ignition config fragment (files, units, kernel args, extensions) | Render |\n32\t| MachineConfigPool | Groups nodes by label selector, tracks update status | Node |\n33\t| ControllerConfig | Cluster-wide config (DNS, proxy, images, certs) | Template |\n34\t| KubeletConfig | Kubelet tuning applied per pool | KubeletConfig |\n35\t| ContainerRuntimeConfig | CRI-O/podman tuning per pool | ContainerRuntimeConfig |\n36\t| MachineConfigNode | Per-node update progress and state | Node/Daemon |\n37\t| MachineOSConfig | OCL build inputs (Containerfile, pool ref) | Build |\n38\t| MachineOSBuild | OCL build execution and status | Build |\n39\t| OSImageStream | OS image references per release | OSImageStream |\n40\t| PinnedImageSet | Pre-pulled container images per pool | PinnedImageSet |\n41\t\n42\t## Update Flow\n43\t\n44\t1. Template Controller renders MachineConfigs from ControllerConfig + templates\n45\t2. KubeletConfig/ContainerRuntimeConfig controllers generate additional MachineConfigs\n46\t3. Render Controller merges all MachineConfigs for each pool into a rendered config\n47\t4. Node Controller assigns target config to nodes, coordinates drain/reboot\n48\t5. MCD (daemon) on each node fetches and applies the config (Ignition, rpm-ostree/bootc, reboot)\n49\t6. For OCL: Build Controller creates Jobs to build layered OS images from MachineOSConfig\n50\t\n51\t## Key Development Commands\n52\t\n53\t```bash\n54\tmake binaries                 # Build all components\n55\tmake test-unit                # Unit tests (no cluster needed)\n56\tmake bootstrap-e2e            # Bootstrap tests via envtest\n57\tmake test-e2e                 # Full e2e (requires cluster)\n58\tmake lint                     # golangci-lint\n59\tmake verify                   # All verification checks\n60\tmake update                   # Regenerate templates from vendor\n61\tmake go-deps                  # go mod tidy + vendor\n62\tmake helpers                  # Build devex tools\n63\t```\n64\t\n65\t## Component-Specific Documentation\n66\t\n67\t- [ai-docs/domain/](ai-docs/domain/) - CRD details and domain model\n68\t- [ai-docs/architecture/components.md](ai-docs/architecture/components.md) - Component internals\n69\t- [ai-docs/decisions/](ai-docs/decisions/) - Architecture decisions\n70\t- [ai-docs/references/ecosystem.md](ai-docs/references/ecosystem.md) - Platform doc links\n71\t- [MCO_DEVELOPMENT.md](MCO_DEVELOPMENT.md) - Development guide\n72\t- [MCO_TESTING.md](MCO_TESTING.md) - Testing guide\n73\t- [docs/HACKING.md](docs/HACKING.md) - Upstream development guide\n74\t\n75\t## Platform Documentation\n76\t\n77\tGeneric OpenShift operator patterns, testing practices, and security guidelines live in the platform hub at `openshift/enhancements/ai-docs/`. This repo documents only MCO-specific knowledge.\n78\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj","session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"d0c9f577-761b-4f69-b20a-fbf48162c318","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:38:36.508Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Check project docs and AI docs for MCO conventions"}
