{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01CGnbryNQ2G2DmgtJgsFrvw", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_01LTn86FPQMyBUXfd4urZCqg", "name": "Read", "input": {"file_path": "/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/MCO_DEVELOPMENT.md"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 2029, "cache_read_input_tokens": 15237, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 2029, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": "toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj", "session_id": "b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6", "uuid": "8c6cf18a-4815-42ec-bcca-a356ee91def8", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcK2D5vtgGdYWj41JJbUQ", "subagent_type": "Explore", "task_description": "Check project docs and AI docs for MCO conventions", "timestamp": "2026-06-22T21:38:37.298Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01LTn86FPQMyBUXfd4urZCqg","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# MCO Development Guide\n2\t\n3\tComponent-specific development guidance. For generic OpenShift operator patterns, see the platform hub (`openshift/enhancements/ai-docs/`). For detailed upstream development instructions, see [docs/HACKING.md](docs/HACKING.md).\n4\t\n5\t## Prerequisites\n6\t\n7\t- Go 1.25.3+\n8\t- podman (for image builds)\n9\t- Access to an OpenShift cluster (for e2e tests)\n10\t- golangci-lint (installed automatically by `make lint`)\n11\t\n12\t## Building\n13\t\n14\t```bash\n15\tmake binaries                          # All 8 binaries\n16\tmake machine-config-operator           # Just the operator\n17\tmake machine-config-daemon             # Just the daemon\n18\tmake machine-config-controller         # Just the controller\n19\tmake image                             # Container image via podman\n20\tmake helpers                           # Developer tools (devex/cmd/)\n21\t```\n22\t\n23\tBuild embeds version info from `git describe`, commit hash, and build date via `hack/build-go.sh`.\n24\t\n25\t## Dependencies\n26\t\n27\t```bash\n28\tmake go-deps                           # go mod tidy + vendor + verify + chmod scripts\n29\t```\n30\t\n31\tVendor directory is committed. All deps must be vendored. After updating `go.mod`, always run `make go-deps`.\n32\t\n33\t## Templates\n34\t\n35\tMCO generates MachineConfigs from Go templates in `templates/` (organized as `common/`, `master/`, `worker/`).\n36\t\n37\t```bash\n38\tmake update                            # Regenerate templates from vendor sources\n39\tmake verify-templates                  # Check templates are current\n40\t```\n41\t\n42\tTemplates are generated from vendored systemd unit files. The Template Controller loads them from `/etc/mcc/templates` at runtime. When modifying templates, run `make update` followed by `make verify-templates`.\n43\t\n44\t## Code Generation\n45\t\n46\tCRD types are defined upstream in `github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/`. MCO vendors these types. To update:\n47\t\n48\t1. Update the `openshift/api` dependency in `go.mod`\n49\t2. Run `make go-deps`\n50\t3. Run `make update` if template sources changed\n51\t\n52\tFeature-gated CRD variants are generated upstream and vendored as `zz_generated.crd-manifests/`.\n53\t\n54\t## Controller Development\n55\t\n56\tAll controllers live in `pkg/controller/`. Shared infrastructure is in `pkg/controller/common/`:\n57\t\n58\t- `controller_context.go` - Shared informer factories, client sets\n59\t- `helpers.go` - MC manipulation, Ignition conversion, annotation helpers\n60\t- `metrics.go` - Prometheus metric registration\n61\t- `featuregates.go` - Feature gate detection\n62\t\n63\tControllers follow the standard pattern: watch resources via informers, enqueue on change, reconcile in `syncHandler`. Use `lib/resourceapply/` for idempotent create-or-update.\n64\t\n65\t## Daemon Development\n66\t\n67\tThe MCD (`pkg/daemon/`) runs on every node. Key files:\n68\t\n69\t- `daemon.go` (~110KB) - Main daemon loop, state machine\n70\t- `update.go` (~135KB) - Update orchestration, reboot/reload decisions\n71\t- `config_drift_monitor.go` - Unauthorized change detection\n72\t- `rpm-ostree.go` / `bootc.go` - OS update backends\n73\t\n74\tTo iterate on MCD without rebuilding the full image, see the \"MCD Iteration\" section in [docs/HACKING.md](docs/HACKING.md) which describes copying the binary directly to nodes.\n75\t\n76\t## Developer Tools\n77\t\n78\tInstall with `make install-helpers`. Located in `devex/cmd/`:\n79\t\n80\t| Tool | Purpose |\n81\t|------|---------|\n82\t| `mcdiff` | Diff two MachineConfigs to understand changes |\n83\t| `mco-push` | Push local MCO binary to a live cluster for testing |\n84\t| `wait-for-mcp` | Block until a MachineConfigPool finishes updating |\n85\t| `mco-builder` | Build custom OS images |\n86\t| `mco-sanitize` | Prepare a cluster for testing |\n87\t| `onclustertesting` | Run tests on a live cluster |\n88\t| `run-on-all-nodes` | Execute a command on all cluster nodes |\n89\t\n90\t## Linting\n91\t\n92\t```bash\n93\tmake lint                              # golangci-lint (10m timeout)\n94\t```\n95\t\n96\tConfig in `.golangci.yml`. Supports `GOTAGS` for conditional compilation. CI produces checkstyle XML and JUnit output.\n97\t\n98\t## Verification\n99\t\n100\t```bash\n101\tmake verify                            # All checks: lint, verify-e2e, verify-templates, verify-helpers\n102\t```\n103\t\n104\tRun before submitting PRs. CI runs these same checks.\n105\t\n106\t## AMI Updates\n107\t\n108\t```bash\n109\tmake update-amis                       # Sync AMI mappings from openshift/installer\n110\t```\n111\t\n112\tUpdates the AMI list in `pkg/controller/bootimage/ami.go` from the installer's region-to-AMI mappings.\n113\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj","session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"cd853dac-8617-4426-9d68-e913d5883e40","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:38:37.302Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Check project docs and AI docs for MCO conventions"}
