{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01J22CWBQbv9BDMMMRGaAKzg","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# MCO Testing Guide\n2\t\n3\tComponent-specific testing guidance. For generic OpenShift testing patterns, see the platform hub (`openshift/enhancements/ai-docs/`).\n4\t\n5\t## Test Suites Overview\n6\t\n7\t| Suite | Command | Cluster Required | Timeout | Description |\n8\t|-------|---------|-----------------|---------|-------------|\n9\t| Unit | `make test-unit` | No | - | Tests in `pkg/`, `cmd/`, `lib/`, `devex/`, `test/helpers/` |\n10\t| Bootstrap | `make bootstrap-e2e` | No (envtest) | - | Verifies bootstrap rendering matches controller rendering |\n11\t| E2E Full | `make test-e2e` | Yes | 190m | All e2e tests (2 shards, parallel) |\n12\t| E2E Shard 1 | `make test-e2e-1of2` | Yes | 100m | MCD, systemd, daemon tests |\n13\t| E2E Shard 2 | `make test-e2e-2of2` | Yes | 100m | Controller, containers, node OS, extensions |\n14\t| Tech Preview | `make test-e2e-techpreview` | Yes | 170m | Feature-gated functionality |\n15\t| Single Node | `make test-e2e-single-node` | Yes (SNO) | - | Single-node cluster scenarios |\n16\t| OCL Shard 1 | `make test-e2e-ocl-1of2` | Yes (OCL) | - | On-cluster layering tests (part 1) |\n17\t| OCL Shard 2 | `make test-e2e-ocl-2of2` | Yes (OCL) | - | On-cluster layering tests (part 2) |\n18\t| IRI | `make test-e2e-iri` | Yes | - | Internal Release Image runtime tests |\n19\t\n20\t## Unit Tests\n21\t\n22\t```bash\n23\tmake test-unit\n24\t```\n25\t\n26\tRuns via `hack/test-unit.sh`. Covers all Go packages except e2e directories. Generates JUnit XML output when `ARTIFACT_DIR` is set. Coverage reports are produced when running in CI.\n27\t\n28\tUnit test files live alongside the code they test (standard Go convention).\n29\t\n30\t## Bootstrap Tests (envtest)\n31\t\n32\t```bash\n33\tmake bootstrap-e2e\n34\t```\n35\t\n36\tUses controller-runtime's envtest (real etcd + kube-apiserver, no full cluster). Verifies that:\n37\t- Bootstrap manifest parsing works correctly\n38\t- Bootstrap-rendered configs match what the controller would produce\n39\t- Pre-built image validation is correct\n40\t\n41\tTest data in `pkg/controller/bootstrap/testdata/bootstrap/`. Kubebuilder tools version: 1.32.1.\n42\t\n43\tThe envtest setup installs MCO CRDs, OpenShift config CRDs, and operator CRDs into the test environment.\n44\t\n45\t## E2E Tests\n46\t\n47\tE2E tests require a running OpenShift cluster with MCO deployed. Tests are split into shards for CI parallelism.\n48\t\n49\t**Framework:** Ginkgo v2 + Gomega  \n50\t**Location:** `test/e2e-*of*/ directories`  \n51\t**Shared code:** `test/e2e-shared-tests/`, `test/helpers/`\n52\t\n53\t### Test Organization\n54\t\n55\t- `test/e2e-1of2/` - Daemon-focused: MCD apply, systemd units, file writes\n56\t- `test/e2e-2of2/` - Controller-focused: rendering, container runtime, node OS, extensions\n57\t- `test/e2e-techpreview/` - Feature-gated tests (require TechPreview cluster)\n58\t- `test/e2e-ocl-*of*/` - On-cluster layering tests (require OCL-enabled cluster)\n59\t\n60\t### Test Helpers (`test/helpers/`)\n61\t\n62\t- `assertions.go` - Custom Gomega matchers and assertion helpers\n63\t- `nodebuilder.go`, `poolbuilder.go` - Fluent builders for test objects\n64\t- `idempotent.go` - Idempotency verification utilities\n65\t- `archiveartifact.go` - Artifact collection for CI\n66\t- `emptyimage.go` - Creates empty container images for testing\n67\t\n68\t### Running E2E Tests Locally\n69\t\n70\t1. Ensure `KUBECONFIG` points to your cluster\n71\t2. Run desired suite: `make test-e2e-1of2`\n72\t3. Tests run sequentially (`-p 1`), fail-fast enabled\n73\t4. Artifacts collected to `ARTIFACT_DIR` if set\n74\t\n75\t## Verification (Compile Checks)\n76\t\n77\t```bash\n78\tmake verify-e2e                        # Compile-check all e2e suites\n79\tmake verify                            # All checks (lint + verify-e2e + verify-templates + verify-helpers)\n80\t```\n81\t\n82\t`verify-e2e` compiles but does not run e2e tests. Catches build errors without requiring a cluster.\n83\t\n84\t## CI Integration\n85\t\n86\tCI uses OpenShift CI (ci-operator). Config in `.ci-operator.yaml`.\n87\t\n88\t- Unit tests and linting run on every PR\n89\t- E2E tests run against provisioned clusters\n90\t- JUnit XML output via `hack/test-with-junit.sh`\n91\t- Artifacts collected to `ARTIFACT_DIR`\n92\t\n93\t## Writing New Tests\n94\t\n95\t**Unit tests:** Place `_test.go` files alongside the code. Use standard Go testing or testify.\n96\t\n97\t**E2E tests:** Add to the appropriate shard directory. Use the test framework:\n98\t```go\n99\timport (\n100\t    \"github.com/openshift/machine-config-operator/test/helpers\"\n101\t    \"github.com/openshift/machine-config-operator/test/framework\"\n102\t)\n103\t```\n104\t\n105\tUse builders from `test/helpers/` for creating test objects. Use `test/e2e-shared-tests/` for test logic shared across suites.\n106\t\n107\t**Bootstrap tests:** Add test cases to `test/e2e-bootstrap/` using envtest framework from `test/framework/envtest.go`.\n108\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj","session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"ebc82152-0172-4f99-8926-75d176f4305c","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:38:37.406Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Check project docs and AI docs for MCO conventions"}
