{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01QnUwkpJmPhxJYbuY2MyQSR", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_012GES1buwWDfpjhqdYF1G7f", "name": "Read", "input": {"file_path": "/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/ai-docs/decisions/adr-002-config-rendering.md"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 4706, "cache_read_input_tokens": 17266, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 4706, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 24}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": "toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj", "session_id": "b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6", "uuid": "4f54afa9-54e3-4dfd-9f1d-9083d58a6f5b", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcK2DHPU6jhVTPvFf2xRu", "subagent_type": "Explore", "task_description": "Check project docs and AI docs for MCO conventions", "timestamp": "2026-06-22T21:38:41.020Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_012GES1buwWDfpjhqdYF1G7f","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# ADR-002: Deterministic Config Rendering\n2\t\n3\t## Status\n4\tActive\n5\t\n6\t## Context\n7\tMultiple MachineConfigs can target a single MachineConfigPool. The system needs a predictable, reproducible way to merge them into one rendered config.\n8\t\n9\t## Decision\n10\tThe Render Controller sorts MachineConfigs by name and merges them sequentially. For file conflicts (same path in multiple MCs), last-writer-wins based on sort order. The rendered config name includes a content hash to avoid unnecessary rollouts when the effective config hasn't changed.\n11\t\n12\tA 5-second render delay batches rapid changes (e.g., multiple MCs created simultaneously) to avoid churn.\n13\t\n14\t## Consequences\n15\t- MC naming matters: alphabetically later MCs override earlier ones for conflicting files\n16\t- Content-based hashing means no-op updates don't trigger node rollouts\n17\t- The render delay means changes are not immediately visible (by design)\n18\t- Render failures set the `RenderDegraded` condition on the pool\n19\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj","session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"8851f7d8-cd4f-4d4c-acb0-4045740a6cc1","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:38:41.022Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Check project docs and AI docs for MCO conventions"}
