{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01R7LouvBULtDMvm1fnN6hWp","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# MCO Ecosystem References\n2\t\n3\t## Platform Documentation\n4\t\n5\tGeneric OpenShift operator patterns, testing practices, and security guidelines live in the platform hub. Reference these for patterns shared across all OpenShift operators:\n6\t\n7\t- **Platform hub:** `openshift/enhancements/ai-docs/` (operator patterns, API conventions, testing standards)\n8\t- **OpenShift API types:** `github.com/openshift/api` (CRD definitions, shared types)\n9\t- **OpenShift library-go:** `github.com/openshift/library-go` (operator scaffolding, controller patterns)\n10\t\n11\t## MCO-Specific References\n12\t\n13\t- **Upstream docs:** `docs/` directory in this repo (HACKING.md, MachineConfig.md, MachineConfigDaemon.md, etc.)\n14\t- **Ignition spec:** [Ignition v2 specification](https://coreos.github.io/ignition/) - config format MCO uses for node configuration\n15\t- **rpm-ostree:** OS update mechanism for traditional RHCOS nodes\n16\t- **bootc:** Container-native OS update mechanism for layered nodes\n17\t\n18\t## Related OpenShift Components\n19\t\n20\t| Component | Relationship to MCO |\n21\t|-----------|-------------------|\n22\t| `openshift/installer` | Creates bootstrap MachineConfigs, provides initial ControllerConfig |\n23\t| `openshift/api` | Defines all MCO CRD types in `machineconfiguration/v1/` |\n24\t| `openshift/client-go` | Generated clients for MCO CRDs |\n25\t| `openshift/library-go` | Operator scaffolding, resource apply patterns |\n26\t| `openshift/cluster-version-operator` | Manages MCO operator deployment, coordinates upgrades |\n27\t| `kubernetes/kubernetes` | Kubelet config, node API, drain utilities |\n28\t| `coreos/ignition` | Config format for node provisioning |\n29\t| `coreos/rpmostree-client-go` | Go client for rpm-ostree operations on nodes |\n30\t\n31\t## CI and Testing\n32\t\n33\t- **CI system:** OpenShift CI (ci-operator), config in `.ci-operator.yaml`\n34\t- **Test framework:** controller-runtime envtest (real etcd + kube-apiserver)\n35\t- **E2E framework:** Ginkgo v2 + Gomega\n36\t- **Kubebuilder tools version:** 1.32.1 (for envtest)\n37\t\n38\t## Internal Tools\n39\t\n40\tDeveloper experience tools in `devex/cmd/`:\n41\t- `mcdiff` - Compare MachineConfigs\n42\t- `mco-push` - Push MCO changes to a live cluster\n43\t- `mco-builder` - Build OS container images\n44\t- `wait-for-mcp` - Wait for MachineConfigPool to finish updating\n45\t- `onclustertesting` - Run tests against a live cluster\n46\t- `run-on-all-nodes` - Execute commands across all cluster nodes\n47\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj","session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"88822268-d890-4fa3-b8a9-d5b728479172","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:38:45.014Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Check project docs and AI docs for MCO conventions"}
