{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_0188WjNdRsAhYgZUbNmFPDp6","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# MCO Domain Model - CRDs\n2\t\n3\tAll CRDs belong to API group `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1`. Types are defined in `vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/`. Compatibility Level 1 (stable within major release, min 12 months).\n4\t\n5\t## MachineConfig\n6\t\n7\tCluster-scoped Ignition config fragment. No status subresource.\n8\t\n9\t**Spec:** `config` (Ignition RawExtension), `kernelArguments` ([]string), `extensions` ([]string), `fips` (bool), `kernelType` (default|realtime|64k-pages), `osImageURL`, `baseOSExtensionsContainerImage`.\n10\t\n11\tMultiple MachineConfigs are merged by the Render Controller into a single rendered config per pool. Merge order is deterministic (sorted by name). Conflicts in file paths use last-writer-wins.\n12\t\n13\t## MachineConfigPool (short: mcp)\n14\t\n15\tGroups nodes via `nodeSelector` and selects MachineConfigs via `machineConfigSelector`. Tracks update rollout status.\n16\t\n17\t**Key spec:** `paused` (bool), `maxUnavailable` (IntOrString), `pinnedImageSets` (max 100), `configuration` (target rendered config).\n18\t\n19\t**Key status:** `machineCount`, `updatedMachineCount`, `readyMachineCount`, `degradedMachineCount`, `conditions` (Updated, Updating, Degraded, NodeDegraded, RenderDegraded, Building, BuildSuccess, BuildFailed, etc.).\n20\t\n21\t**Validation rules:** machineCount >= updatedMachineCount, machineCount >= readyMachineCount, etc.\n22\t\n23\tDefault pools: `master`, `worker`. Custom pools inherit from worker via `machineConfigSelector`.\n24\t\n25\t## ControllerConfig\n26\t\n27\tCluster-wide configuration consumed by Template Controller to generate base MachineConfigs.\n28\t\n29\t**Key spec:** `clusterDNSIP`, `rootCAData`, `kubeAPIServerServingCAData`, `additionalTrustBundle`, `pullSecret`, `images` (map), `baseOSContainerImage`, `releaseImage`, `proxy`, `infra`, `dns`, `ipFamilies` (IPv4|IPv6|DualStack|DualStackIPv6Primary), `networkType`.\n30\t\n31\t**Status conditions:** TemplateControllerRunning, TemplateControllerCompleted, TemplateControllerFailing.\n32\t\n33\t## KubeletConfig\n34\t\n35\tApplies upstream kubelet configuration overrides per pool.\n36\t\n37\t**Key spec:** `machineConfigPoolSelector` (LabelSelector), `kubeletConfig` (RawExtension - upstream KubeletConfiguration), `autoSizingReserved` (bool), `logLevel` (0-10), `tlsSecurityProfile`.\n38\t\n39\tController generates a MachineConfig with the merged kubelet config and drops file at `/etc/kubernetes/kubelet.conf`.\n40\t\n41\t## ContainerRuntimeConfig (short: ctrcfg)\n42\t\n43\tTunes CRI-O and container runtime settings per pool.\n44\t\n45\t**Key spec:** `machineConfigPoolSelector`, `containerRuntimeConfig` with fields: `pidsLimit`, `logLevel` (fatal..debug), `logSizeMax` (>= 8192), `overlaySize` (default 10GB), `defaultRuntime` (crun|runc), `additionalLayerStores` (max 5), `additionalImageStores` (max 10), `additionalArtifactStores` (max 10).\n46\t\n47\tStore paths validated: absolute, 1-256 chars, pattern `^/[a-zA-Z0-9/._-]+$`, no consecutive slashes.\n48\t\n49\t## MachineConfigNode\n50\t\n51\tPer-node update tracking. Created/managed by Node Controller and updated by MCD.\n52\t\n53\t**Spec:** `configVersion.desired` (target MC ref), `pool.name`, `node.name`.\n54\t\n55\t**Status conditions:** Updated, UpdatePrepared, UpdateExecuted, UpdatePostActionComplete, UpdateComplete, Resumed, UpdateCompatible, AppliedFiles, AppliedFilesAndOS, Cordoned, Uncordoned, Drained, RebootedNode, ReloadedCRIO, PinnedImageSetsDegraded, PinnedImageSetsProgressing.\n56\t\n57\t## MachineOSConfig\n58\t\n59\tDefines on-cluster layering (OCL) build inputs for a pool.\n60\t\n61\t**Key spec:** `machineConfigPool` (ref), `buildInputs`, `containerFile` ([]ContainerFile with `content` and optional `containerfileArch`).\n62\t\n63\t## MachineOSBuild\n64\t\n65\tTracks execution of an OCL build job.\n66\t\n67\t**Key spec:** `machineOSConfig` (ref), `machineConfig` (ref).\n68\t\n69\t**Key status:** `digestedImagePushSpec` (built image), `builder.job` (Job ref with name/namespace).\n70\t\n71\t## OSImageStream\n72\t\n73\tOS image references for the release. Managed by the osimagestream binary.\n74\t\n75\t**Status:** `defaultStream`, `availableStreams` ([]OSImageStreamSpec with `name`, `osImage`, `osExtensionsImage`).\n76\t\n77\t## PinnedImageSet\n78\t\n79\tPre-pulls container images to nodes in matching pools.\n80\t\n81\t**Spec:** `machineConfigPoolSelector` (LabelSelector), `pinnedImages` ([]PinnedImage with `name`).\n82\t\n83\t## Feature-Gated CRD Variants\n84\t\n85\tCRDs ship in multiple variants for feature gates: Default, DevPreviewNoUpgrade, CustomNoUpgrade, TechPreviewNoUpgrade, OKD, Hypershift, SelfManagedHA. Located in `vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/zz_generated.crd-manifests/`.\n86\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01LvxZJ4Yutvn6tN8jjixSiJ","session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"e1be85b8-f132-4194-8a7c-c8fa3f13efa0","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:39:06.622Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Find MachineConfigPool and KubeletConfig examples and best practices"}
