g/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/mco_registry.go:394:\t\tlogger.Infof(\"Wait for worker pool to be updated\")\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/mco_password.go:171:\t\tlogger.Infof(\"Number of AuthorizedKeys configured for worker nodes: %d\", len(workerKeys))\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/mco_password.go:179:\t\t\tlogger.Infof(\"Checking authorized keys file in node:%s\", worker.GetName())\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/mco_password.go:180:\t\t\tcheckAuthorizedKeyInNode(worker, workerKeys)\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1185:// GetCompactCompatiblePool returns worker pool if the cluster is not compact/SNO. Else it will return master pool or custom pool if worker pool is empty.\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1190://\t\tIf custom pools exist\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1191://\t\t\tIf any custom pool has nodes, we return the custom pool\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1192://\t    \tElse (all custom pools are empty) we are in a Compact/SNO cluster with extra empty custom pools, we return master\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1193://\t\tElse (worker pool is empty and there is no custom pool) we are in a Compact/SNO cluster, we return master\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1211:\t// The cluster is not Compact/SNO but the the worker pool is empty. All nodes have been moved to one or several custom pool\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1214:\t\t\tlogger.Infof(\"Worker pool is empty, but there is a custom pool with nodes. Proposing %s MCP for testing\", mcp.GetName())\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1223:// GetCompactCompatibleOrCustomPool returns compact compatible pool or creates custom pool that will use the same stream as the worker pool\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1257:\t\tlogger.Infof(\"No CoreOs nodes in the worker pool. Using master pool for testing\")\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1264:// CreateCustomMCPWithStreamByLabel Creates a new custom MCP using the nodes in the worker pool with the given label. If numNodes < 0, we will add all existing nodes to the custom pool\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1265:// If numNodes == 0, no node will be added to the new custom pool.\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1275:\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"the worker MCP only has %d nodes, it is not possible to take %d nodes from worker pool to create a custom pool\",\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1316:\t\treturn NewMachineConfigPool(oc, name), fmt.Errorf(\"a %d nodes custom pool cannot be created because there are only %d nodes in the %s pool\",\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1327:\terr := NewMCOTemplate(oc, \"custom-machine-config-pool-osimagestream.yaml\").Create(\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1342:\t\tlogger.Infof(\"Node %s added to custom pool %s\", n.GetName(), customMcp.GetName())\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1400:\t// Wait for worker MCP to be updated before removing the custom pool\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/machineconfigpool.go:1401:\t// in order to make sure that no node has any annotation pointing to resources that depend on the custom pool that we want to delete","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj","session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"c93651a1-ca5d-4d84-becb-67280c571e24","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:40:01.491Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Check project docs and AI docs for MCO conventions"}
