{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01LvxZJ4Yutvn6tN8jjixSiJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a comprehensive report of everything found in the repository:\n\n---\n\n## 1. MachineConfigPool YAML Examples\n\n### Built-in Pool Manifests (deployed by MCO itself)\n\n**Worker pool** - `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/worker.machineconfigpool.yaml`\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfigPool\nmetadata:\n  name: worker\n  labels:\n    \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/mco-built-in\": \"\"\n    \"pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker\": \"\"\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\": \"worker\"\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/worker: \"\"\n```\n\n**Master pool** - `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/master.machineconfigpool.yaml`\nSame structure, with additional `operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/required-for-upgrade: \"\"` label.\n\n**Arbiter pool** - `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/arbiter.machineconfigpool.yaml`\nSame structure with arbiter-specific labels and role.\n\n### Custom Pool that Inherits from Worker\n\nThe canonical pattern for inheriting from the worker pool uses `matchExpressions` with `operator: In` to include both `worker` and the custom role. Found in two places:\n\n**docs/custom-pools.md** (the infra example):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfigPool\nmetadata:\n  name: infra\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchExpressions:\n      - {key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role, operator: In, values: [worker, infra]}\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/infra: \"\"\n```\n\n**test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-machine-config-pool.yaml** (OpenShift Template form, parameterized):\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchExpressions:\n      - { key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role, operator: In, values: [ worker,\"${NAME}\" ] }\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/${NAME}: \"\"\n```\n\n**test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-machine-config-pool-osimagestream.yaml** - Same template with the `osImageStream` field added for pinning the pool to a specific RHEL version.\n\n### Other Example/Test MCP Files\n\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/etcd.machineconfigpool.yaml` - etcd pool using simple `matchLabels` (does not inherit worker)\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` - minimal worker example (no built-in labels)\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/master.machineconfigpool.yaml` - minimal master example\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/bootstrap/testdata/bootstrap/layered-worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` - pool that uses `matchLabels` only (no worker inheritance, not a custom pool)\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-pools/test-pool.yaml` - shows the full status fields structure\n\n---\n\n## 2. KubeletConfig YAML Examples\n\nAll KubeletConfig examples are in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/`:\n\n**generic-kubelet-config.yaml** - Template using the standard `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/${POOL}` label selector (preferred for OCP 4.6+):\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/${POOL}: ''\n  kubeletConfig: ${{KUBELETCONFIG}}\n```\n\n**change-maxpods-kubelet-config.yaml** - Sets `maxPods: 500`:\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/${POOL}: ''\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 500\n```\n\n**custom-tls-profile-kubelet-config.yaml** - Uses `tlsSecurityProfile` with custom ciphers and TLS version:\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  tlsSecurityProfile:\n    type: Custom\n    custom:\n      ciphers:\n      - ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256\n      - ECDHE-ECDSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305\n      - ECDHE-RSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305\n      - ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256\n      minTLSVersion: VersionTLS11\n```\n\n**examples/kubeletconfig.crd.yaml** - Minimal example with a custom label selector (pre-4.6 style):\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      custom-kubelet: small-pods\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Documentation on Best Practices\n\n### docs/custom-pools.md\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md`\n\nThis is the primary best-practices document for MachineConfigPools. Key guidance:\n\n- Custom pools inherit from `worker` by using `matchExpressions` with `operator: In, values: [worker, <custom>]`\n- Label the node first: `oc label node <node> node-role.kubernetes.io/infra=`\n- A node can be part of at most one pool\n- Custom pools on master nodes are NOT supported\n- To remove the worker role from a purely infra node: `oc label node <node> node-role.kubernetes.io/worker-` (the node still inherits worker MachineConfigs because the pool selector includes worker)\n- Removing a custom pool: un-label nodes first, wait for worker pool to reconcile, then delete the MCP and any custom MCs\n- Updates roll out concurrently across pools (1 node per pool at a time by default)\n\n### docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md`\n\nKey guidance:\n\n- In OCP 4.6+, use the `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/{worker|master}` label on the `machineConfigPoolSelector`; for older clusters or custom pools, add a custom label to the MCP's metadata\n- The `logLevel` field (0-10, default 2) increases IO/CPU on all nodes in the pool\n- `autoSizingReserved: true` automatically calculates system-reserved CPU and memory per node\n- KubeletConfig fields are validated by kubelet itself; invalid values may render nodes unusable\n- Upon deletion of a KubeletConfig, the default kubelet config is restored\n- The controller generates a `99-[role]-kubelet-managed` MachineConfig, which triggers a node drain and reboot\n\n### docs/MachineConfigController.md\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfigController.md`\n\nExplains the MCO architecture. Key points:\n- `maxUnavailable` defaults to 1; set to a higher number or percentage for faster rollouts (respects PDBs); use `paused: true` to stop updates entirely\n- MachineConfigs are merged in lexicographic order by name; last writer wins on conflicts\n- The `99-[role]-kubelet-managed` MachineConfig is auto-generated by KubeletConfigController\n\n### docs/FAQ.md\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/FAQ.md`\n\nNotable notes: watch worker rollout with `oc describe machineconfigpool/worker`; MCO only blocks upgrades on control-plane nodes by default.\n\n---\n\n## 4. API Types / Schema\n\n### Primary source: vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go`\n\n**MachineConfigPoolSpec** (lines 399-469):\n| Field | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `machineConfigSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Selects MachineConfig objects |\n| `nodeSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Selects nodes |\n| `paused` | `bool` | Stops updates; cannot use maxUnavailable=0 for this purpose |\n| `maxUnavailable` | `*intstr.IntOrString` | Default: 1; accepts integer or percentage |\n| `configuration` | `MachineConfigPoolStatusConfiguration` | Target rendered config ref |\n| `pinnedImageSets` | `[]PinnedImageSetRef` | Max 100; pre-pulls images to nodes |\n| `osImageStream` | `OSImageStreamReference` | Feature-gated (OSStreams); pins pool to a specific RHEL stream |\n\n**MachineConfigPoolStatus** (lines 499-552): tracks `machineCount`, `updatedMachineCount`, `readyMachineCount`, `unavailableMachineCount`, `degradedMachineCount`, and `conditions` (Updated, Updating, Degraded, NodeDegraded, RenderDegraded, ImageBuildDegraded, PinnedImageSetsDegraded).\n\n**KubeletConfigSpec** (lines 736-771):\n| Field | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `autoSizingReserved` | `*bool` | Auto-calculates system-reserved CPU/memory; default true for workers, false for masters |\n| `logLevel` | `*int32` | Kubelet log verbosity 0-10, default 2 |\n| `machineConfigPoolSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Targets which pool(s) this applies to |\n| `kubeletConfig` | `*runtime.RawExtension` | Upstream KubeletConfiguration fields; values validated by kubelet |\n| `tlsSecurityProfile` | `*configv1.TLSSecurityProfile` | Old/Intermediate/Modern/Custom; defaults to cluster apiservers setting |\n\n### CRD YAML manifests (vendor)\n\nFully-rendered CRD schemas live in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/zz_generated.crd-manifests/`:\n- `0000_80_machine-config_01_machineconfigpools-Default.crd.yaml` - Default feature set\n- `0000_80_machine-config_01_kubeletconfigs-Default.crd.yaml` - Default feature set\n- Additional variants for `CustomNoUpgrade`, `DevPreviewNoUpgrade`, `TechPreviewNoUpgrade`, `OKD`\n\n### Important constants (types.go, lines 14-17):\n```go\nconst MachineConfigRoleLabelKey = \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\"\nconst KubeletConfigRoleLabelPrefix = \"pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/\"\n```\n\nThe `KubeletConfigRoleLabelPrefix` combined with the pool name (e.g., `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker`) is the modern (OCP 4.6+) label to use in `machineConfigPoolSelector.matchLabels` on a KubeletConfig, and it must also be present as a label on the corresponding MachineConfigPool."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"1c78db64-f56f-4f3c-b902-9b5645d87593","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:40:01.738Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In the machine-config-operator repository at /home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator, find:\n1. Example YAML files for MachineConfigPool (especially ones that inherit from worker pool)\n2. Example YAML files for KubeletConfig\n3. Any documentation about best practices for creating these resources (check docs/, README, and any .md files)\n4. The API types/schema for MachineConfigPool and KubeletConfig (look in pkg/apis or vendor)\n\nSearch breadth: very thorough","agentId":"ac035d4a244162191","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a comprehensive report of everything found in the repository:\n\n---\n\n## 1. MachineConfigPool YAML Examples\n\n### Built-in Pool Manifests (deployed by MCO itself)\n\n**Worker pool** - `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/worker.machineconfigpool.yaml`\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfigPool\nmetadata:\n  name: worker\n  labels:\n    \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/mco-built-in\": \"\"\n    \"pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker\": \"\"\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\": \"worker\"\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/worker: \"\"\n```\n\n**Master pool** - `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/master.machineconfigpool.yaml`\nSame structure, with additional `operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/required-for-upgrade: \"\"` label.\n\n**Arbiter pool** - `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/arbiter.machineconfigpool.yaml`\nSame structure with arbiter-specific labels and role.\n\n### Custom Pool that Inherits from Worker\n\nThe canonical pattern for inheriting from the worker pool uses `matchExpressions` with `operator: In` to include both `worker` and the custom role. Found in two places:\n\n**docs/custom-pools.md** (the infra example):\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfigPool\nmetadata:\n  name: infra\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchExpressions:\n      - {key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role, operator: In, values: [worker, infra]}\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/infra: \"\"\n```\n\n**test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-machine-config-pool.yaml** (OpenShift Template form, parameterized):\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchExpressions:\n      - { key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role, operator: In, values: [ worker,\"${NAME}\" ] }\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/${NAME}: \"\"\n```\n\n**test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-machine-config-pool-osimagestream.yaml** - Same template with the `osImageStream` field added for pinning the pool to a specific RHEL version.\n\n### Other Example/Test MCP Files\n\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/etcd.machineconfigpool.yaml` - etcd pool using simple `matchLabels` (does not inherit worker)\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` - minimal worker example (no built-in labels)\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/master.machineconfigpool.yaml` - minimal master example\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/bootstrap/testdata/bootstrap/layered-worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` - pool that uses `matchLabels` only (no worker inheritance, not a custom pool)\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-pools/test-pool.yaml` - shows the full status fields structure\n\n---\n\n## 2. KubeletConfig YAML Examples\n\nAll KubeletConfig examples are in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/`:\n\n**generic-kubelet-config.yaml** - Template using the standard `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/${POOL}` label selector (preferred for OCP 4.6+):\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/${POOL}: ''\n  kubeletConfig: ${{KUBELETCONFIG}}\n```\n\n**change-maxpods-kubelet-config.yaml** - Sets `maxPods: 500`:\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/${POOL}: ''\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 500\n```\n\n**custom-tls-profile-kubelet-config.yaml** - Uses `tlsSecurityProfile` with custom ciphers and TLS version:\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n  tlsSecurityProfile:\n    type: Custom\n    custom:\n      ciphers:\n      - ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256\n      - ECDHE-ECDSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305\n      - ECDHE-RSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305\n      - ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256\n      minTLSVersion: VersionTLS11\n```\n\n**examples/kubeletconfig.crd.yaml** - Minimal example with a custom label selector (pre-4.6 style):\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      custom-kubelet: small-pods\n  kubeletConfig:\n    maxPods: 100\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Documentation on Best Practices\n\n### docs/custom-pools.md\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md`\n\nThis is the primary best-practices document for MachineConfigPools. Key guidance:\n\n- Custom pools inherit from `worker` by using `matchExpressions` with `operator: In, values: [worker, <custom>]`\n- Label the node first: `oc label node <node> node-role.kubernetes.io/infra=`\n- A node can be part of at most one pool\n- Custom pools on master nodes are NOT supported\n- To remove the worker role from a purely infra node: `oc label node <node> node-role.kubernetes.io/worker-` (the node still inherits worker MachineConfigs because the pool selector includes worker)\n- Removing a custom pool: un-label nodes first, wait for worker pool to reconcile, then delete the MCP and any custom MCs\n- Updates roll out concurrently across pools (1 node per pool at a time by default)\n\n### docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md`\n\nKey guidance:\n\n- In OCP 4.6+, use the `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/{worker|master}` label on the `machineConfigPoolSelector`; for older clusters or custom pools, add a custom label to the MCP's metadata\n- The `logLevel` field (0-10, default 2) increases IO/CPU on all nodes in the pool\n- `autoSizingReserved: true` automatically calculates system-reserved CPU and memory per node\n- KubeletConfig fields are validated by kubelet itself; invalid values may render nodes unusable\n- Upon deletion of a KubeletConfig, the default kubelet config is restored\n- The controller generates a `99-[role]-kubelet-managed` MachineConfig, which triggers a node drain and reboot\n\n### docs/MachineConfigController.md\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfigController.md`\n\nExplains the MCO architecture. Key points:\n- `maxUnavailable` defaults to 1; set to a higher number or percentage for faster rollouts (respects PDBs); use `paused: true` to stop updates entirely\n- MachineConfigs are merged in lexicographic order by name; last writer wins on conflicts\n- The `99-[role]-kubelet-managed` MachineConfig is auto-generated by KubeletConfigController\n\n### docs/FAQ.md\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/FAQ.md`\n\nNotable notes: watch worker rollout with `oc describe machineconfigpool/worker`; MCO only blocks upgrades on control-plane nodes by default.\n\n---\n\n## 4. API Types / Schema\n\n### Primary source: vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go`\n\n**MachineConfigPoolSpec** (lines 399-469):\n| Field | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `machineConfigSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Selects MachineConfig objects |\n| `nodeSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Selects nodes |\n| `paused` | `bool` | Stops updates; cannot use maxUnavailable=0 for this purpose |\n| `maxUnavailable` | `*intstr.IntOrString` | Default: 1; accepts integer or percentage |\n| `configuration` | `MachineConfigPoolStatusConfiguration` | Target rendered config ref |\n| `pinnedImageSets` | `[]PinnedImageSetRef` | Max 100; pre-pulls images to nodes |\n| `osImageStream` | `OSImageStreamReference` | Feature-gated (OSStreams); pins pool to a specific RHEL stream |\n\n**MachineConfigPoolStatus** (lines 499-552): tracks `machineCount`, `updatedMachineCount`, `readyMachineCount`, `unavailableMachineCount`, `degradedMachineCount`, and `conditions` (Updated, Updating, Degraded, NodeDegraded, RenderDegraded, ImageBuildDegraded, PinnedImageSetsDegraded).\n\n**KubeletConfigSpec** (lines 736-771):\n| Field | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `autoSizingReserved` | `*bool` | Auto-calculates system-reserved CPU/memory; default true for workers, false for masters |\n| `logLevel` | `*int32` | Kubelet log verbosity 0-10, default 2 |\n| `machineConfigPoolSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Targets which pool(s) this applies to |\n| `kubeletConfig` | `*runtime.RawExtension` | Upstream KubeletConfiguration fields; values validated by kubelet |\n| `tlsSecurityProfile` | `*configv1.TLSSecurityProfile` | Old/Intermediate/Modern/Custom; defaults to cluster apiservers setting |\n\n### CRD YAML manifests (vendor)\n\nFully-rendered CRD schemas live in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/zz_generated.crd-manifests/`:\n- `0000_80_machine-config_01_machineconfigpools-Default.crd.yaml` - Default feature set\n- `0000_80_machine-config_01_kubeletconfigs-Default.crd.yaml` - Default feature set\n- Additional variants for `CustomNoUpgrade`, `DevPreviewNoUpgrade`, `TechPreviewNoUpgrade`, `OKD`\n\n### Important constants (types.go, lines 14-17):\n```go\nconst MachineConfigRoleLabelKey = \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\"\nconst KubeletConfigRoleLabelPrefix = \"pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/\"\n```\n\nThe `KubeletConfigRoleLabelPrefix` combined with the pool name (e.g., `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker`) is the modern (OCP 4.6+) label to use in `machineConfigPoolSelector.matchLabels` on a KubeletConfig, and it must also be present as a label on the corresponding MachineConfigPool."}],"resolvedModel":"claude-sonnet-4-6","totalDurationMs":93307,"totalTokens":59013,"totalToolUseCount":29,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2701,"cache_read_input_tokens":53160,"output_tokens":3151,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2701},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":22,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":7,"editFileCount":0,"linesAdded":0,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}}}
