{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_019vEgQH3hX4988zQX1XenmP","type":"tool_result","content":"/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md:7:**Note:** Custom pools on master nodes are not supported by MCO. For more detail, see [Custom pool on master node](#Custom-pool-on-master-node)\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md:14:$ oc label node ip-10-0-130-218.us-west-1.compute.internal node-role.kubernetes.io/infra=\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md:50:      node-role.kubernetes.io/infra: \"\"\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md:126:$ oc label node ip-10-0-130-218.us-west-1.compute.internal node-role.kubernetes.io/infra-\n/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md:170:Custom pool on a node having master role is not supported. `oc label node` will apply the new custom role to the target master node but MCO will not apply changes specific to the custom pool. Error can be seen in the Machine Config Controller pod logs. This behaviour is to make sure that control plane nodes remain stable.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj","session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"e83d25be-1688-43de-8703-6b0d4d141991","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:40:11.768Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Check project docs and AI docs for MCO conventions"}
