{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FVjokv2fbL5yUVz4FEGkAj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me compile the final report.\n\n---\n\nHere is a complete summary of all documented best practices and constraints for MachineConfigPool and KubeletConfig resources in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## MachineConfigPool: Best Practices and Constraints\n\n### Pool Inheritance from Worker\n\n**The core rule** (enforced by a ValidatingAdmissionPolicy): every custom MachineConfigPool must inherit from the `worker` pool. This means the `machineConfigSelector` must match for a `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker` label.\n\nThe policy file at `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/machineconfigcontroller/custom-machine-config-pool-selector-validatingadmissionpolicy.yaml` enforces this with `failurePolicy: Fail` and `validationActions: [Deny]`. The exact CEL expression requires that the `machineConfigSelector` either:\n- Uses `matchLabels` with role = `master`, `worker`, or `arbiter`\n- Uses `matchExpressions` with `key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role`, `operator: In`, and `\"worker\"` in values\n\nThe canonical pattern from `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md` for a custom `infra` pool:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchExpressions:\n      - {key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role, operator: In, values: [worker,infra]}\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/infra: \"\"\n```\n\nThis means the custom pool picks up all MachineConfigs labeled for `worker` AND all labeled for `infra`. Any change to the worker pool rolls out to the custom pool as well (including OS upgrades).\n\n### Default Pools\n\n- Names: `master` and `worker` (defined as `MachineConfigPoolMaster` and `MachineConfigPoolWorker` in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/common/constants.go`).\n- The third built-in pool is `arbiter` (`MachineConfigPoolArbiter`).\n- `IsCustomPool()` returns true for any pool that is not `master`, `worker`, or `arbiter`.\n\n### Pool Labels\n\nEvery MachineConfigPool carries a label of the form `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/<poolname>: \"\"`. This label is what KubeletConfig and ContainerRuntimeConfig use in their `machineConfigPoolSelector.matchLabels` to target a specific pool. The constant `KubeletConfigRoleLabelPrefix = \"pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/\"` is defined in the vendored API types at `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go`.\n\nWorker pool example label: `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"`\nMaster pool example label: `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/master: \"\"`\n\n### Custom Pool on Master Nodes: Not Supported\n\nExplicitly documented in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md`: custom pools on nodes with the master role are not supported. The label can be applied but MCO will not apply custom-pool-specific configs to master nodes - this is intentional to keep control plane stable.\n\n### OSImageStream Inheritance\n\nFor OSImageStream, custom pools inherit the worker pool's setting if no explicit `osImageStream.Name` is set. This is implemented in `GetEffectiveOSImageStreamName()` in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/common/helpers.go` (lines 1484-1508).\n\n### MachineConfig Naming for Pools\n\n- MachineConfigs are labeled with `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: <rolename>` to target a pool (constant `MachineConfigRoleLabelKey`).\n- Merge order is alphabetical by MC name; alphabetically later MCs win on file conflicts.\n- Rendered configs are named with prefix `rendered-` plus a content hash.\n\n### Node Membership\n\nA node can be a member of at most one MachineConfigPool at any given time.\n\n---\n\n## KubeletConfig: Constraints\n\n### Forbidden Fields (Controller-Enforced)\n\nThe function `validateUserKubeletConfig()` in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/kubelet-config/helpers.go` (lines 350-399) explicitly rejects any KubeletConfig CR that sets these fields inside `spec.kubeletConfig`:\n\n| Field | Reason |\n|---|---|\n| `cgroupDriver` | Controlled by the cluster; setting it can make the node unrecoverable |\n| `clusterDNS` | Cluster-managed |\n| `clusterDomain` | Cluster-managed |\n| `featureGates` | Must be set only through the OpenShift FeatureGate API, not here |\n| `staticPodPath` | Not user-settable |\n| `failSwapOn` | Not user-settable |\n| `memorySwap.swapBehavior` | Not user-settable |\n\nAdditional mutual-exclusion rule: `autoSizingReserved: true` and `systemReserved` cannot both be set in the same KubeletConfig CR. If both are present, the controller errors.\n\nAdditional cross-field validation: if both `systemReservedCgroup` and `systemCgroups` are non-empty, they must be equal.\n\n### Limit on Number of KubeletConfig CRs Per Pool\n\nA maximum of **10** KubeletConfig CRs can exist that target the same pool. This is enforced in the `getManagedKubeletConfigKey()` function in helpers.go (lines 200-320). The constant `MaxMCNameSuffix = 9` in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/common/constants.go` encodes this (the suffixes go from 0-9, inclusive, yielding 10 slots). Exceeding this produces the error: `\"max number of supported kubelet config (10) has been reached. Please delete old kubelet configs before retrying\"`.\n\n### LogLevel Constraint\n\n`spec.logLevel` must be in the range `[0, 10]` (validated explicitly). Defaults to 2 if not set. Higher values consume more IO and CPU on all nodes in the pool.\n\n### Feature Gates\n\nFeature gates must not be set in `spec.kubeletConfig.featureGates`. Instead, use the OpenShift `FeatureGate` cluster-scoped singleton named `cluster`. The KubeletConfig controller overrides any user-supplied feature gates with the cluster-level feature gate settings.\n\n### Generated MachineConfig Naming\n\nThe controller generates MachineConfig objects with names following this pattern:\n- First KubeletConfig per pool: `99-<poolname>-generated-kubelet`\n- Subsequent ones: `99-<poolname>-generated-kubelet-<N>` where N is 1-9\n\nThe prefix constant is `managedKubeletConfigKeyPrefix = \"99\"`. The higher suffix number means higher priority (alphabetically later = last-writer-wins on file conflicts). The generated file is placed at `/etc/kubernetes/kubelet.conf`.\n\n### Pool Selection\n\nKubeletConfig targets pools via `spec.machineConfigPoolSelector.matchLabels` using the `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/<poolname>: \"\"` label. Example for worker:\n```yaml\nmachineConfigPoolSelector:\n  matchLabels:\n    pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: \"\"\n```\n\n### autoSizingReserved\n\nWhen `spec.autoSizingReserved: true` is set (with no `systemReserved` in kubeletConfig), the controller writes a dynamic node-sizing configuration. Default system-reserved fallback values are `memory=1Gi`, `cpu=500m`, `ephemeral-storage=1Gi`.\n\n---\n\n## Naming Conventions Summary\n\n| Resource | Convention |\n|---|---|\n| Custom MachineConfigPool | Any name except `master`, `worker`, `arbiter` |\n| Pool label on MCP metadata | `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/<name>: \"\"` |\n| MachineConfig role label | `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: <rolename>` |\n| Rendered MachineConfig | `rendered-<poolname>-<hash>` |\n| KubeletConfig-generated MC (first) | `99-<poolname>-generated-kubelet` |\n| KubeletConfig-generated MC (subsequent) | `99-<poolname>-generated-kubelet-<1-9>` |\n| Node role for custom pool nodes | `node-role.kubernetes.io/<rolename>: \"\"` |\n\n---\n\n## Key Source Files\n\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/custom-pools.md` - Full custom pool walkthrough\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/KubeletConfigDesign.md` - KubeletConfig design spec\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/machineconfigcontroller/custom-machine-config-pool-selector-validatingadmissionpolicy.yaml` - Admission policy enforcing worker inheritance\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/kubelet-config/helpers.go` - `validateUserKubeletConfig()` (forbidden fields), `getManagedKubeletConfigKey()` (10-CR limit, naming)\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/common/constants.go` - `MachineConfigPoolWorker`, `MachineConfigPoolMaster`, `MachineConfigRoleLabel`, `MaxMCNameSuffix`\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/common/helpers.go` - `IsCustomPool()`, `GetEffectiveOSImageStreamName()`\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/ai-docs/domain/crds.md` - CRD field reference\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/ai-docs/decisions/adr-002-config-rendering.md` - Render ordering rules"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6","uuid":"9be6569d-8443-436e-a176-2e33acd2c96c","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:40:58.061Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In the machine-config-operator repository at /home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator, look at:\n1. The ai-docs/ directory - read all files there\n2. AGENTS.md\n3. MCO_DEVELOPMENT.md\n4. MCO_TESTING.md\n5. Any docs/ directory\n\nI need to understand the documented best practices and constraints for MachineConfigPool and KubeletConfig resources, especially:\n- How pools should inher