{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_012dv8SRBN8pKnDagggHYzhj", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Please approve the file writes. Here's what each file contains and why:\n\n---\n\n**`gpu-worker-machineconfigpool.yaml`**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfigPool\nmetadata:\n  name: gpu-worker\n  labels:\n    pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/gpu-worker: \"\"   # required for KubeletConfig targeting\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchExpressions:\n      - key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\n        operator: In\n        values:\n          - worker\n          - gpu-worker   # inherits all worker MachineConfigs + gpu-worker-specific ones\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/gpu-worker: \"\"\n```\n\n**`gpu-worker-kubeletconfig.yaml`**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: KubeletConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: gpu-worker-kubelet\nspec:\n  autoSizingReserved: false   # must be false \u2014 mutually exclusive with systemReserved\n  machineConfigPoolSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/gpu-worker: \"\"\n  kubeletConfig:\n    cpuManagerPolicy: static\n    systemReserved:\n      memory: 2Gi\n```\n\n---\n\n**Key design decisions driven by project constraints:**\n\n| Decision | Source |\n|---|---|\n| `matchExpressions` with `values: [worker, gpu-worker]` | `ValidatingAdmissionPolicy` at `manifests/machineconfigcontroller/custom-machine-config-pool-selector-validatingadmissionpolicy.yaml` \u2014 `failurePolicy: Fail` will block any MCP that doesn't include `worker` |\n| `pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/gpu-worker: \"\"` label on MCP | Required by KubeletConfig controller to find the pool (`KubeletConfigRoleLabelPrefix` constant in `vendor/.../types.go`) |\n| `autoSizingReserved: false` | `validateUserKubeletConfig()` in `pkg/controller/kubelet-config/helpers.go` rejects CRs that set both `autoSizingReserved: true` and `systemReserved`; workers default to `true` |\n| No forbidden fields (`cgroupDriver`, `clusterDNS`, etc.) | Same validation function |\n\nThe controller will generate a `99-gpu-worker-generated-kubelet` MachineConfig, which triggers a drain+reboot rolling out one node at a time across the pool."}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 2430, "cache_read_input_tokens": 40430, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 2430, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "b36bfe9c-b5ba-4115-8f21-75f99f58dba6", "uuid": "3085b2fa-7e5d-4f8c-9600-e9359e32fad8", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcK2S4WS6rL6utHxMLB2D", "timestamp": "2026-06-22T21:41:41.552Z"}
